cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about instance segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach that uses a neural network for iterative contour deformation, which involves learning-based techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes the use of circular convolution for structured feature learning, which is a technique commonly used in graph-based methods, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the efficiency of the proposed approach, which suggests that it could be used in real-time applications, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a two-stage pipeline for instance segmentation, which involves both computer vision and robotics techniques, making cs.RO (Robotics) another possible sub-category.
